✨10 things I wish I knew before I started shaving my face✨
✅SAVE FOR LATER✅

1- NEVER SHAVE ON DRY SKIN. Always use a lubricant like aloe vera gel or moisturiser or face oil or snail mucin essence before shaving .

2-SANITIZE your razor before and after shaving. I use rubbing alcohol or wipes to clean the razor.

3-Never use the razor in your undereye area. The skin is very sensitive and it’s very likely to get a cut very easily.

4- Always shave in the direction of hair growth. Use short strokes. 

5- Use ice to soothe your skin post shaving. And use moisturiser after that. It will prevent razor bumps. 

6-Change your razor after every 7-8 shaves. It will prevent spread of bacteria.

7- Avoid shaving if you have active acne. 

8- Always shave your nose , it reduces the appearance of black heads.

9- Never apply any actives post shaving atleast for 1day. Don’t forget your SPF the next day.

10- Don’t exfoliate post shaving for atleast 2-3 days to avoid redness and irritation.
